The paper deals with satellite image classification using machine learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed framework involves the use of Deep Belief Networks, which is a popular deep learning algorithm, and hence, the paper could also be categorized under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of unsupervised learning techniques over traditional supervised learning techniques, which could be categorized under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses statistical analysis to evaluate the proposed approach, which could be categorized under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
